Subject: Re: SuSE40528-Virtual disk does not dynamically attach

Hi Olaf,

What do you think of the patch below?  Basically if you read
/sys/bus/vio/drivers/viodasd/probe then the driver probes for newly
attached disks and returns the names of any found.

Do you think this is sufficient?

This patch is against 2.6.6-bk3, but should apply to just about any recent
tree ...

-- 
Cheers,
Stephen Rothwell                    sfr@au.ibm.com
IBM OzLabs Linux Technology Centre

